A mathematical description of biology that I think captures much of it is:

Life = Information × Memory × Feedback × Time

Remove any one term and the system loses its biological character.

And for vision specifically:

Seeing is not detecting light. Seeing is transforming light into useful differences.

That transformation chain—the sequence of translations—is arguably where most of the intelligence resides. The photons themselves are simple. The interpretation is where the magic happens.